title: Life: Poem XXI A Book
creator: Emily Dickinson
description: Poem XXI: "A Book", by Emily Dickinson, read by the wonderful podcasters at the Podcasters Across Borders 2006 conference, in Kingston, Ontario, June 23-24, 2006. Read by: Andy Doan, Arthur Masters, Bob Goyetche, Ben Kenny, Bruce Murray, Betty Rock, Cat, Cathi Bond, Craig Newell, Charlotte Scott, Dave Delaney, Matt, Dan Meisner, David Newland, Evan Thornton, Isabelle Michaud, Joe Chisholm, John Bignell, Hugh McGuire, Jay Moonah, Julien Smith, Krash Coarse, Leesa Barnes, Maurizio Ortolani, Michael Bhardwaj, Mark Blevis, Matthew Forsythe, Neil Gorman, Nora Young, Sonya Buyting, Samuel Genera, Sylvain Grand-Maison, Sarah MacGreggor, Shane, Tim Campbell, Tristan Homer, Tom Luscher, Tod Maffin, Tony Piper, Wendy Eliott. reviews.reviewbody: I can not believe this got posted. The first poem insulted my senses with loud obnoxious background noise. Didn't go any further. Listen for yourself.
reviews.reviewtitle: First poem sounds like it was recorded in a bar.
